news.title: West Bengal government sanctions Rs 2.9 crore for LED project
news.para: Government officials said that the agency that will be engaged for the work will also need to monitor the entire installation for one year.

news.title: Cement makers to add 150-160 MTPA capacity by fiscal 2028: Crisil
news.para: As much as 70-75 MT of the capacity addition is expected to be commissioned next fiscal, with 50-55% concentrated in the eastern and central regions. Large players will account for 50-55% of the planned capacity addition.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers to launch projects worth Rs 9,000 crore by FY25
news.para: Project launches by Kolte-Patil Developers in Pune will account for approximately Rs 6,400 crore and will be in micro-markets like Kiwale, Pimple Nilakh, Baner, Kharadi, Hinjewadi, and NIBM Road.

news.title: India has REIT-ready office supply of Rs 5.8-6.2 lakh crore across top seven cities: ICRA
news.para: The REIT office supply has increased by 3.3 times in the last five years to ~82 million sq ft across the top seven cities i.e. Bengaluru, Chennai, Delhi-NCR, Hyderabad, Kolkata, Mumbai and Pune in India.

news.title: DRA Homes to invest Rs 2,000 crore in FY24-25
news.para: The outlay will be funded by further equity, internal accruals, family office investments and structured debt by DRA Homes.

news.title: Guwahati civic body to seize homes of property tax defaulters
news.para: GMC has issued more than 50 warrants against such tax defaulters. Their properties will be seized by the corporation if the tax is not paid on time, said Dahal.

news.title: Dehradun police collect Rs 1 crore fine from over 1,000 landlords in verification drive
news.para: Senior superintendent of police (SSP), Dehradun, Ajai Singh, informed that during the drive, 278 people failed to produce any valid documents to support their verification.

news.title: Mumbai: Housing society to pay Rs 1.5 lakh compensation to joint shop owners
news.para: ​Ruling in favour of the joint owners, Dahisar residents, Jasmin Kapadia and Ketan Parmar, the commission said that the complainants have established that the society is liable for deficiency in services.

news.title: Noida residents want government to stop scheme to auction land in housing sectors
news.para: The residents pointed out that this would increase the rate of land in residential sectors and make them affordable only for the affluent few.

news.title: Maharashtra may need ECI nod to announce ready reckoner rates on April 1
news.para: Ready reckoner (RR) rate is the state govt’s assessments of property value, on the basis of which stamp duty and registration charges are paid.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Extra flats in Express Garden, 25 GDA engineers are under scanner
news.para: On Saturday, senior GDA officials told TOI that the committee submitted its report recently and notices have been served to 25 officials, deputed mostly at the development authority's enforcement wing between 2008 and 2012.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks Mahira Homes to deposit deficit funds in RERA accounts
news.para: H-Rera chairman Arun Kumar has announced a three-step action plan for delayed affordable housing projects of the developer and offered relief to aggrieved homebuyers.

news.title: Four years on, Dwarka expressway link is set for a revamp
news.para: The Rs 11.8 crore project will involve reconstruction of the main carriageway, surface drain and footpaths by Nov this year. The metropolitan authority will also construct slip roads, streetlights at junctions and road safety furniture such as road studs, cat’s eyes and bollards.

news.title: Mumbai: Phase 2 of Bhendi Bazaar redevelopment project at advanced stage
news.para: An SBUT spokesperson said, "Two towers of 53 storeys each are being constructed replacing 23 old and dilapidated buildings on a plot of approximately 1.34 acres. Sector 6 will house more than 1,250 families and around 270 businesses."

news.title: Over 100 buy flats at Bengaluru development body mela
news.para: “More than 100 participants paid the initial deposit amount and booked their chosen apartments,” said a BDA official. Fifty allottees were issued allotment letters during the mela.

news.title: Shop rentals dip in CBD areas of Kolkata in face of hawker pressure
news.para: Traders, real estate agents and market committees TOI spoke to attributed the sharp decline in rent to rampant encroachment by hawkers, not only the pavements but also the carriageway.

news.title: Nashik: NDCC bank starts process of Renukadevi society’s property auction to recover dues
news.para: The NDCC Bank has called the parties that wish to participate in the auction to visit the property so that they can participate in the bidding process.

news.title: PMAY in Ranchi runs out of funds, houses left incomplete
news.para: Ranchi Municipal Corporation approved 12,587 applications for the scheme since 2016 to FY2021-2022, providing initial funds to 8,000 beneficiaries.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to set up registry camps now in Noida every Sunday
news.para: Officials said those who fail to attend the Sunday camps could get the registries executed at the office of the stamps and registry department on other days of the week.

news.title: US: Single family housing sees a rise in permits in January
news.para: Single-family housing starts, which account for the bulk of homebuilding, dropped 4.7% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.004 million units last month, the Commerce Department's Census Bureau said on Friday.
